events.name: IWD
events.description:
We are excited to announce that Google and Women Techmakers at Delta University are supporting and empowering women in technology through the global event series in celebration of International Women’s Day (IWD). Women Techmakers IWD meetups are led by the incredible WTM Leads around the world but all GDGs (and all genders) are encouraged to participate.
The Women Techmakers 2018 International Women’s Day Celebration (IWD) will be held for the first time at Delta University in Mansoura city (MU).
Women Techmakers is Google’s brand and global program for women in technology. We provide visibility, community, and resources for women in technology to drive innovation and participation in the field. The activities of Women Techmakers are designed to promote creation of conditions for participation of women in the field of high technology.
The Women Techmakers IWD consists of two parts. In the first half of the day, participants will get acquainted with the activities of women, who work in the IT field. They will share their experience on implementing IT projects, including in large foreign companies. In the second part, the participants of the Women Techmakers IWD will be able to take part in seminars and master classes and will gain knowledge on project management and development of various IT products.

Conference (about 10 conferences)
Workshops (about 4 workshops)
Topics: more than 24 hours of pure Google technologies.
- Android
- Web
- Cloud Computing

events.name: Build Actions For Your Community
events.description:
• What we'll do
Join us for a free two days, Google Developers Group at Delta on building custom Actions for Google.
Learn to build apps for the Google Assistant.

Agenda:

9:00 AM-9:30AM Registration

9:30 AM-10:30 AM Introductions and announcements

10:30 AM-11:00 AM Engaging with the Google Assistant: What is this and why do we care? An overview of the various things that the Google Assistant can do. Why is voice powerful and what things can we do with it?

11:00 AM-12:00 PM Engaging with the Google Assistant: Building Awesome Actions, a high-level view. How do we, as Developers, design and build for the Google Assistant? A high-level view of the components that make it up and the concepts we need to think about.

12:00 PM-1:00 PM - Components for Awesome Actions. You can build an Action on any platform, but Google makes it easier.

1:00 PM-2:00 PM Lunch

2:00 PM-3:00 PM Start your own project

4:30 PM Wrap up

Bring your laptop and... take your ticket!

See you soon!

events.description:
I/O Extended 18 GDG Delta Event lets you experience the magic and innovation of Google I/O remotely. Part viewing experience and part community building, I/O extended event includes everything from the Google I/O content to local developer. Be inspired by tech world's latest web, mobile and social breakthroughs to create simple life improving technologies and viable businesses among a rich and diverse community of cutting edge developers.

Google Developers Codelabs provide a guided, tutorial, hands-on coding experience. Most codelabs will step you through the process of building a small application, or adding a new feature to an existing application. They cover a wide range of topics such as Android Wear, Google Compute Engine,Flutter, and Google APIs on iOS.

Google Developer Group at Delta University the day off with a Google-inspired codelab that gives developers a chance to get their hands in some of the latest technology. Later, it all culminates in our live streaming of the keynote from Google I/O 2018 straight from the Shoreline Amphitheatre Mountain View, California.

PROGRAMME
12:00: Registration - for everyone not participating in the Codelab ,make sure to bring your laptop for training and code lap

12:30: Opening - Akram Zeyada, Google I/O, is here to get you properly introduced to Google io and GDG Global Summit – don’t miss this

13:00: Codelab: flutter - Ahmed Abu Eldahab Chief Technology Officer (CTO) at Savvy Arabia
Founder and team leader at Egyptian Google Flutter Community got you covered a lot of things about flutter and making Codelab when we get into deep recurrent neural network

14:00: Food and networking – try out one of many activities like climbing, VR 3D painting or daring parkour

14:15:back to building flutter

15:00: Group Photo – make sure to bring your laptop for training and code lap

15:15: Short break - get snacks , a coke and some popcorn

15:30: Recorded sessions from Shoreline Amphitheatre Mountain View, California – what we’ve all been waiting for since last year

16:00: Angular - Nader khaled

16:30: Afterparty – fill your glass, get talking – it’s time to have fun!

#Google_IO_Extended
#io18
#GDG
#GDG_Delta_University

events.name: Cloud Next Extended
events.description:
Cloud Next Extended
Next Extended brings together developer communities around the world to take part in the Next ‘18 experience, either during the conference or even after!
These events run from late July to November 9. Next Extended allows local developers to access exciting Next ‘18 content and engage with the community through local speakers, activities, and hands-on labs.
Communities across the globe host external Extended events. Google Developers supports and recognizes GDG and Google Cloud Developer Community chapters that host these events but does not own or manage them.

events.name: Mansoura University Week for Entrepreneurship-women techmakers
events.description:
Mansoura University Week for Entrepreneurship and Emerging Companies

Under the patronage of Mr. Ashraf Abdelbaset Al-Qaim, President of Mansoura University, the University Center for Professional Development organizes the Mansoura University for Entrepreneurship and Entrepreneurship Week as a window for the students and graduates of the university on the life of entrepreneurs. The first week of the week, from 13 to 17 November 2018, aims at spreading the culture of entrepreneurship and helping students and graduates to translate their ideas into real projects.

This week's events will be held during the World Entrepreneurship Week, where we will present a series of seminars and workshops for the definition of entrepreneurship and the stages of transforming the idea into a project. Successful models will be presented to entrepreneurs:
- The concept of entrepreneurship
- Entrepreneur specifications
- How to generate innovative entrepreneurial ideas
- Translating ideas into real projects
- Effective marketing skills
- Project Finance
- Introducing grant and funding entities
- Financial and administrative aspects of start-up companies
- Use technology to support entrepreneurs
- Inspiring models and success stories

➡ Dev Ecosystem Study Jams
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Study Jams are study groups complementary to Google Developers Roadshow MENA events, ran by Dev Ecosystem MENA with content from Google Developers.

The objective of the Study Jams is to increase the technical competence of the members of our community through face-to-face courses.

These trainings give the members of our community a series of skills that can be used for personal and professional development.

Join us in the second edition of Study Jams MENA!

--------------------------------------------------------------
##########################################
--------------------------------------------------------------

➡ Training Of Trainers
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
TOT is important, because any trainer needs two separate sets of skills and knowledge; The topic they are teaching (subject matter expertise); And the know-how of transferring that information to the student (instructional expertise). Instructors need both of these sets of skills, and we train you on both.

The goal of the Training of Trainers (TOT) process is to give new trainers the background knowledge, skills and practical experience to provide communities the training and technical assistance they need.

These trainings ensures that communities have their qualified local trainers, who can conduct these workshops in a scalable & self-sustainable way.

➡You can enroll now with commitment & dedication!
